#- The King§0
§0beneath the mountains,§0
§0
§0The King§0
§0of carven stone,§0
§0
§0The lord§0
§0of silver fountains,§0
§0
§0Shall come§0
§0into his own!§0

#- His crown§0
§0shall be upholden,§0
§0
§0His harp§0
§0shall be restrung,§0
§0
§0His halls§0
§0shall echo golden,§0
§0
§0To songs§0
§0of yore re-sung.
#- The woods shall§0
§0wave on mountains,§0
§0
§0And grass§0
§0beneath the sun;§0
§0
§0His wealth shall§0
§0flow in fountains,§0
§0
§0And the rivers§0
§0golden run.
#- The streams shall§0
§0run in gladness,§0
§0
§0The lakes shall§0
§0shine and burn,§0
§0
§0All sorrow§0
§0fail and sadness,§0
§0
§0At the§0
§0Mountain-king's return.
